{"TopicId":161850,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Advanced Avionics: Single Jet and single Rocket Engine Spaceplane","CreatedByName":"StanK","CreatedById":130429,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-09T13:59:01Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"StanK","CreatedById":130429,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-09T13:59:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo follow up on the famous K Prize, this challenge asks you to show off your master spaceplane design and flying skills. Build a spaceplane capable of reaching orbit, and returning safely using a single jet, and a single rocket engine. I have found this an interesting limitation that makes spaceplane design a lot harder. Mostly because the trust vectors are no longer trivially aligned with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E. Enjoy!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRules:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nThe spaceplane must follow the rules as defined by the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/11189-the-k-prize-100-reusable-spaceplane-to-orbit-and-back/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EK Prize\u003C/a\u003E. In short: a horizontal take-off stock \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E that can reach orbit(pe\u0026gt;70km) and land again in one piece.\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nThe provisions of the K Prize do apply to this challenge too.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nUse exactly 1 jet engine - defined as an engine that requires intake air and liquid fuel to run.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nUse exactly 1 rocket engine - defined as an engine that runs entirely on on-board fuel. An ion engine is also allowed.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nRapier engines are allowed, but cannot switch mode during the flight and as such operate entirely as a jet, or entirely as a rocket engine.\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nMerging/clipping/offsetting the two engines together into one is also not allowed (this is not much different from a mode switching rapier).\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nPlease remember to take pictures or a video as proof and for our enjoyment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdvanced Aviators:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/65767-scarecrow/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002265767\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/65767-scarecrow/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Scarecrow\u003C/a\u003E - Rotate the engines, why not?\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158362-martian-emigrant/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022158362\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158362-martian-emigrant/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Martian Emigrant\u003C/a\u003E - The perfect case for a Thud\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112154-goduranus/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022112154\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112154-goduranus/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@goduranus\u003C/a\u003E - Reverse trust in reverse\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130429-stank/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022130429\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/130429-stank/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@StanK\u003C/a\u003E - Me \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112611-wanderfound/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022112611\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112611-wanderfound/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Wanderfound\u003C/a\u003E - With spare seats\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/175397-foobar/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022175397\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/175397-foobar/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@foobar\u003C/a\u003E - You can see through it\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/177994-tsgaerospace/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022177994\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/177994-tsgaerospace/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@tsgaerospace\u003C/a\u003E - Pushed up into space\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/169112-rosvall/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022169112\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/169112-rosvall/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Rosvall\u003C/a\u003E - Rolling into space\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150623-michaldon/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150623\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150623-michaldon/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@michal.don\u003C/a\u003E - Pancake to accelerate!\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n...can proudly wear their badge:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tOXiKuk.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/tOXiKuk.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022EApOkVF.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/EApOkVF.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00224FfH0X9.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/4FfH0X9.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022sotdxk4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/sotdxk4.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have done a few times in past versions. To show it is still possible in 1.3 below is my own new entry:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlbum: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/dDIOT\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/dDIOT\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022u7PJ7z4.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/u7PJ7z4.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-12T17:43:10Z\u0022 title=\u002207/12/2017 05:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 12, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by StanK\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdded another Advanced Aviator\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Human Person","CreatedById":174876,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-09T15:00:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can simply put the rocket engine (e.g. A terrier) on the front of your plane and flip it to circularize.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-09T15:01:26Z\u0022 title=\u002206/09/2017 03:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 9, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Physics Student\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StanK","CreatedById":130429,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-09T19:54:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223085916\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497020428\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174876\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Physics Student\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Physics Student said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can simply put the rocket engine (e.g. A terrier) on the front of your plane and flip it to circularize.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a valid way to engage in this challenge. Although from my experience, \u0022simply\u0022 is not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll have a dig in my archives and see if I can find the images for it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sivonen","CreatedById":165197,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-09T20:07:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the engines are to be on top of each other, you \u003Cs\u003Emust\u003C/s\u003E can rotate the engines to point to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E. Then your plane doesn\u0027t rotate when accelerating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst the jet, tanks full, set rocket engines thrust limit to 0, rotate the jet so thrust vector points exactly away from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThen set jet thrust to 0, rocket to 100, empty \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Liquid Fuel\u0022\u003ELF\u003C/abbr\u003E tanks used by jet and align the rocket engine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEmpty all tanks, adjust wing position so that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E is behind \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E and go to space and back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StanK","CreatedById":130429,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-10T13:38:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFlipping at high velocity, from my archives:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlbum: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/PzIyi\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/PzIyi\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022RB21n9y.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/RB21n9y.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022TH68lk8.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/TH68lk8.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223086183\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497038834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165197\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sivonen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/9/2017 at 9:07 PM, Sivonen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the engines are to be on top of each other, you \u003Cs\u003Emust\u003C/s\u003E can rotate the engines to point to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis could definitely work, but it will mess with the aerodynamics too. So I\u0027ll believe it when I see it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-08T17:17:56Z\u0022 title=\u002207/08/2017 05:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 8, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by StanK\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eimgur troubles\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sivonen","CreatedById":165197,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-10T14:47:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust a quick build to prove the concept. 40x180km orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/a/tcohS\u0022 style=\u0022height:466px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-10T14:48:19Z\u0022 title=\u002206/10/2017 02:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Sivonen\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StanK","CreatedById":130429,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-11T10:29:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice proof of concept \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/165197-sivonen/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022165197\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/165197-sivonen/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sivonen\u003C/a\u003E, too bad fuel ran out just before orbit. I love the unusual shape, I have not seen an outline like that before.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-11T16:34:51Z\u0022 title=\u002206/11/2017 04:34  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by StanK\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Emissed a word\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"goduranus","CreatedById":112154,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-11T12:46:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can put the turbofan on the nose in reverse, and use reverse thrust to move forward.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso the jet can be attached to the back node of a rocket, and moved to clip into the rocket, and both engines can work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-11T12:51:58Z\u0022 title=\u002206/11/2017 12:51  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 11, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by goduranus\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow","CreatedById":65767,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-11T13:20:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just stacked the rocket and jet engine in line.\u00A0 Job done. 72k x 90k orbit with fuel to spare.\u00A0 Engines used are LV-T45 rocket and JX-4 Ramjet jet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022simpleSSTO.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.88qv.com/KSP/simpleSSTO.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StanK","CreatedById":130429,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-11T16:34:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCongratulations \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/65767-scarecrow/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002265767\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/65767-scarecrow/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Scarecrow\u003C/a\u003E! You are the first to successfully finish the challenge. Coincidentally, I also grant you the honour to be the last do do so with a merged-rocket-and-jet or DIY-rapier solution. I will update the rules, and no longer allow this in the future - my apologies for this (also feel free to suggest how to clearly put this in a rule if my rule isn\u0027t).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223087840\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497185190\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022112154\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022goduranus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, goduranus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can put the turbofan on the nose in reverse, and use reverse thrust to move forward.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s a great idea \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112154-goduranus/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022112154\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112154-goduranus/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@goduranus\u003C/a\u003E, I did not think of that. Will you have enough trust and high altitude/velocity to create a viable \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E though? Would be nice to see.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223087840\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497185190\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022112154\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022goduranus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, goduranus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso the jet can be attached to the back node of a rocket, and moved to clip into the rocket, and both engines can work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs above, I\u0027ll update the rules for this as it is too similar to using a switching rapier.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Martian Emigrant","CreatedById":158362,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-11T18:33:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey all Kerbalites.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere is my entry:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nImgur: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/VtyXu\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/VtyXu\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA basic jet. The wings and jet fuel are positioned high to raise the COG.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is in the hope of lessening the angle on the rocket motor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe atmospheric engine is more forgiving as the aircraft uses control surfaces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/16dbt6U.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002216dbt6U.png\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/16dbt6U.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ziK8POU.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ziK8POUg.png\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ziK8POUg.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/DO53OQB.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022DO53OQBg.png\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/DO53OQBg.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EThe prototype did \u00BE of an orbit before burning retrograde. \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ELining up with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/gCOBZ1m.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022gCOBZ1mg.png\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/gCOBZ1mg.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EJeb re-lighted the engines as he was a bit short.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/xqyxhPt.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022xqyxhPt.png\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/xqyxhPt.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EHe landed about 1 km from the runway but never tapped the brakes and coasted all the way to the hangar.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/tQIJqgE.png\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 title=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tQIJqgE.png\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/tQIJqgE.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EME\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-12T03:13:16Z\u0022 title=\u002206/12/2017 03:13  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 12, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Martian Emigrant\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow","CreatedById":65767,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T14:34:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew submission to meet the spirit of the challenge.\u00A0 Basically the same airframe as before, but with the engines now definitely mounted separately.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n78k x 150k orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022simpleSSTO2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.88qv.com/KSP/simpleSSTO2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"goduranus","CreatedById":112154,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T16:19:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrontal reverse thrust turbofan plane, 71x70 km orbit with 21 liquid fuel remaining.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/XjvLais.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022XjvLais.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T16:25:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223089169\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497284395\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022112154\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022goduranus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, goduranus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrontal reverse thrust turbofan plane, 71x70 km orbit with 21 liquid fuel remaining.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/XjvLais.jpg\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XjvLais.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/XjvLais.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReverse thrust! Very, very nice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"goduranus","CreatedById":112154,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T16:26:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI learned that trick from YouTuber Jolly Rogers Aerospace\u0027s most recent stream.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StanK","CreatedById":130429,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T17:51:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice one \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158362-martian-emigrant/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022158362\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158362-martian-emigrant/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Martian Emigrant\u003C/a\u003E, it\u0027s always good to see a practical use of the \u0022thud\u0022 engine. And it can drive along too, you say? Mission complete!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the second entry \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/65767-scarecrow/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002265767\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/65767-scarecrow/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Scarecrow\u003C/a\u003E, that is exactly showing off the spaceplane design skills to keep that working that we are looking for. I didn\u0027t check before, but did you manage to land it \u003Cs\u003Esafely\u003C/s\u003E in one piece as\u00A0 well?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrontal reverse turbofan. I did not believe it until I saw it \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112154-goduranus/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022112154\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112154-goduranus/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@goduranus\u003C/a\u003E. Getting anything into space using a turbofans and atomic engines shows craftsmanship on it\u0027s own right. Did it also manage to come back to Kerbin\u0027s surface?\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"goduranus","CreatedById":112154,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T17:55:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHad a pilot error so it broke on landing, but design itself works. The frontal engine held up to the re-entry heat, and had 10 units of fuel after slowing down to flight speeds. I could do a proper landing when I get around to it..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StanK","CreatedById":130429,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T18:02:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood to hear the turbofan can survive re-entry, that would be the hard one to fix. My own attempt required some quick saving/loading as well to get the landing in-one-piece.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow","CreatedById":65767,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-12T19:16:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll returned safely, only thing missing is the fuel used to get there and back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022simpleSSTO3.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.88qv.com/KSP/simpleSSTO3.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022simpleSSTO4.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.88qv.com/KSP/simpleSSTO4.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022simpleSSTO5.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.88qv.com/KSP/simpleSSTO5.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"goduranus","CreatedById":112154,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-13T10:24:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI launched the reverse thrust craft again because I kept on missing the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E and needed more fuel to cross range, this time makes it into orbit with ~130 fuel. The great thing about the reverse turbofan is that it can be reversed again to slow down quickly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/GIYfydM.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022GIYfydM.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ErZ55hb.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022ErZ55hb.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/hEtGgCB.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022hEtGgCB.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wanderfound","CreatedById":112611,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-15T12:47:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother vertical-stack build:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://imgur.com/a/ZSqot\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://imgur.com/a/ZSqot\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/a/ZSqot\u0022 style=\u0022height:528px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-07-10T13:53:07Z\u0022 title=\u002207/10/2017 01:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 10, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Wanderfound\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StanK","CreatedById":130429,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-15T21:42:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is a good looking one \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112611-wanderfound/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022112611\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112611-wanderfound/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Wanderfound\u003C/a\u003E. Well done! And good to see there\u0027s room for passengers to enjoy the ride as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112154-goduranus/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022112154\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/112154-goduranus/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@goduranus\u003C/a\u003E for showing it can land. And having \u003Cs\u003Ereversed\u003C/s\u003E normal trust to break is a bonus.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo show you my gratitude, you and previous Advanced Aviators can now wear a badge:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tOXiKuk.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/tOXiKuk.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foobar","CreatedById":175397,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-17T15:02:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorking on a proof-of-concept ... TIL planes with giant holes in them can get to space no problem. Honestly didn\u0027t think this would work.\u00A0I\u0027ll follow up with a real mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ozB94FJ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ozB94FJ.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"foobar","CreatedById":175397,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-17T19:59:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223094784\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161850\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497711723\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175397\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022foobar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, foobar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll follow up with a real mission.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http://imgur.com/a/iDyed\u0022 style=\u0022height:499px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StanK","CreatedById":130429,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T17:58:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is an awesome entry \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/175397-foobar/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022175397\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/175397-foobar/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@foobar\u003C/a\u003E. Congratulations on completing the challenge, and adding a new style for single jet\u002Brocket development.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}